Cases in various countries:
Asia
---
- Pakistan (Lahore, Punjab province). 19 Dec 2011. The Pakistan
Medical Association (PMA) has vowed to support the Punjab government
in an anti-quackery drive, claiming that thousands of quacks were
running clinics in the city and were responsible for the deaths of 200
dengue patients.
http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2011%5C12%5C19%5Cstory_19-12-2011_pg7_19.

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map sowing the location of Lahore
in Punjab province can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1kdh. -
Mod.TY]

Latin America
---
- Mexico (Jalisco state). 22 Dec 2011. Only 168 cases of dengue fever
have been registered in the state of Jalisco during 2011, a massive
improvement on the official figures of the past 3 years. The
metropolitan area of Guadalajara reported the highest number of cases,
(more than 60), followed by Puerto Vallarta (40), noted Leandro
Hernandez Barrios of the Jalisco Health Department this week. Cases of
dengue fever have been reported in 26 of Jalisco's 126 municipalities.
At the same time in 2010, the SSJ [Jalisco Health Secretariat] had
received confirmed reports of 1172 cases in the state. Only 12 of the
168 reported cases were DHF.
http://ww.guadalajarareporter.com/news-mainmenu-82/regional-mainmenu-85/30214-dengue-cases-drop-dramatically.html

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of
Jalisco state can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1A1z. -
Mod.TY]

- Brazil (Goias state). 22 Dec 2011. Since January [2011, to the
present], 41 000 cases have been reported. In all of 2010, 115 000
dengue cases were registered, [so thi is] a reduction of 65 percent
from last year [2010]. In 2011, there were 5 dengue deaths in Goiania.
A reduction in dengue deaths was also observed in the state, from 93
in 2010 to 29 this year.
http://g1.globo.com/goias/noticia/2011/12/casos-de-dengue-registrados-recuam-65-em-goias-no-ano-de-2011.html
[in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map sowing the location of Goias
state can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1xid. - Mod.TY]

- Brazil (Rio Claro, São Paulo state). 22 Dec 2011. This year [2011],
1767 positive dengue cases were registered. The combination of rain
and hot weather makes the environment excellent for the [vector]
mosquito _Aedes aegypti_. The Center for Zoonosis Control indicated
that 88 percent of the breeding sites [of this mosquito] are in
residences.
http://www.canalrioclaro.com.br/?pg=noticia&id=6121 [in Portuguese,
trans. Mod.TY]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map sowing the location of Rio
Claro in São Paulo state can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/1A1D. - Mod.TY]

- Brazil (Rio Branco, Acre state). 21 Dec 2011. Rio Branco was among
the cities with greatest dengue epidemic risk, according to a survey
by the Ministry of Health. To provide an idea, in the past 2 weeks the
number of dengue cases tripled, reaching 90 registered cases.
http://www.oriobranco.net/saude/21405-diretora-da-vigilancia-epidemiologica-de-rio-branco-alerta-populacao-para-o-combate-a-dengue-com-a-chegada-as-chuvas-intensas.html
[in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of Rio
Branco in Acre state can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1A1v.
- Mod.TY]

- Brazil (Alagoas state). 22 Dec 2011. From 1 Jan-20 Dec [2011], 10
647 dengue cases were registered in 99 cities in Alagoas state. There
have been 10 deaths and 278 serious cases of the disease. In 2010,
there were nearly 5 times more dengue cases in the state -- 54 200.
http://www.alagoas24horas.com.br/conteudo/?vEditoria=Sa%FAde&vCod=116640
[in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map sowing the location of
Alagoas state can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1A1C. -
Mod.TY]

Pacific
---
Marshall Islands. 23 Dec 2011. The World Health Organisation says the
dengue fever outbreak in the Marshall Islands is almost over. The
World Health Organisation's Dr Eric Nilles says the region is on a
heightened state of alert because of an outbreak of [dengue virus]
type 2 in the Marshall Islands and the Federated States of Micronesia.
However, he says the outbreak has peaked from a maximum number of 50
per day to less than 5 per day since 19 Dec [2011].
http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=65231.

[Maps showing the location of the Marshall Islands in the Pacific
Ocean can be accessed at
http://travel.nationalgeographic.com/travel/countries/marshall-islands-map/
and http://healthmap.org/r/1n1p. - Mod.TY]
